Fig. 4B and the inset in Fig. 4B indicate that the ECL intensity decreases with increasing PSA concentration and that the decrease in ECL intensity can be categorized as ΔI, or I0 - I, where I0 is the ECL intensity from PSA-Ab1/GQD/TiO2 and I is the ECL intensity from MNP/CdTe/Ab2-PSA-Ab1/GQD/TiO2. The ΔI was found to be logarithmically linearly proportional to the concentration of PSA in a wide concentration range from 1.0 fg mL−1 to 1.0 pg mL−1, with a detection limit of 1.0 fg mL−1 (S/N = 3). The linear regression equation was ΔI = 222.9 + 3096.8 log(CPSA (fg mL
−1
)) (R2 = 0.996).
